    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean, a lot of analysts argue that radical changes in the electorate can lead to cultural friction or a loss of \"traditional\" values that these institutions were built on. wouldn't a rapid influx of people with different cultural or social priorities potentially destabilize the existing political consensus and cause more chaos in the system?",
